#                                    (Rust, 5,412★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/rhaiscript/rhai
# author : Stephen Chung (schungx) + the rhaiscript collective (fork of
#          Jonathan Turner's ChaiScript-inspired ergo lang)
# license: Apache-2.0 OR MIT (dual)
#
# Source-direct completion: every CLI surface below is verbatim from
# src/bin/{rhai-dbg,rhai-repl,rhai-run}.rs on the rhai tip — each binary's
# `main()` calls `env::args().skip(1)` (raw argv, no clap) and takes
# positional `.rhai` script paths.  rhai-repl additionally exposes
# interactive REPL commands (help/quit/exit/keys/history/scope/strict/
# optimize/functions/json/ast/astu/!!/!<#>/!<text>/!?<text>) typed at the
# rustyline prompt — those are REPL inputs, not shell argv, so they're
# documented here for reference but not completed as zsh args.
#
# Direct deps from src/bin/*.rs `use` lines (selected):
#   rhai::Engine                     ← canonical Rust embedded scripting
#                                      engine (this axis) — Stephen Chung
#   rhai::debugger::{BreakPoint,
#                    DebuggerCommand,
#                    DebuggerEvent}  (rhai-dbg only)
#   rustyline                       ← canonical Rust readline replacement
#                                      with vi/emacs bindings, history
#                                      search, and event-driven keybind
#                                      registration (rhai-repl only)
#                                      — Katyo Aliev + the kkawakam
#                                      collective
#
# rhai is a tiny embeddable scripting language designed for Rust apps that
# need user-extensible behavior — game scripting, config DSLs, plugin
# systems, data transformation pipelines.  Syntax is JavaScript-ish with
# strong Rust-side typing; Engine::register_fn binds Rust functions into
# Rhai with zero boxing; closures are first-class; modules support
# import/export; the Engine itself is sandboxable (no_std, no_float,
# no_function compile-time feature gates).
#
# === AXIS 169 OPENER — embedded scripting languages ecosystem ===========
# Axis position: Rust=224 OPENS Axis 169 at slot 1/0/0.  Canonical Rust
# embeddable scripting language is `rhai` by Stephen Chung — designed
# from scratch for "fast, safe, embeddable" — values are 16-byte
# `Dynamic` (3-word smartptr), error type is one `Box<EvalAltResult>`,
# AST is interned + optimized at compile time, and the entire interpreter
# is `no_std` capable.  De-facto choice when an app wants Rust + scripts
# without dragging in V8/QuickJS/Lua-C.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=224     ← THIS FILE              (axis 169 OPENS, slot 1/0/0)
#   Go=224       ← next round              (axis 169 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=224  ← round after             (axis 169 CLOSES at triple-224, slot 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_rhai-run() {
    case "$service" in
        rhai-dbg)
            # rhai-dbg takes exactly ONE script file (env::args().nth(1))
            _arguments \
                '1:Rhai script file to debug (single-stepping under rhai::debugger):_files -g "*.rhai"'
            ;;
        rhai-repl)
            # rhai-repl takes ZERO OR MORE script files to pre-load into REPL scope
            # (env::args().skip(1) — each file is canonicalized then read into the
            # Engine before the rustyline prompt starts; pre-loaded scripts share
            # the global Scope so REPL input can reference their functions/vars).
            # Interactive REPL commands (typed at the prompt, NOT at the shell):
            #   help / quit / exit / keys / history / scope / strict
            #   optimize / functions / json / ast / astu
            #   !! / !<#> / !<text> / !?<text>
            _arguments \
                '*:Rhai script file to pre-load into REPL scope:_files -g "*.rhai"'
            ;;
        rhai-run|*)
            # rhai-run iterates env::args().skip(1) and runs each script in turn
            # under a fresh `Engine::new()` per file with OptimizationLevel::Simple
            _arguments \
                '*:Rhai script file to run:_files -g "*.rhai"'
            ;;
    esac
}

_rhai-run "$@"
